Package: clustack
Title: A Stacking Approach to Spatial and Spatio-Temporal Cluster Detection
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Maria", "Kamenetsky", , "maria.kamenetsky@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: `clustack` is an R package basedthat implements a stacking approach to spatial cluster detection. Based on the Poisson-likelihood, single-cluster models are combined using likelihood-based weights, resulting in cell-wise stacked relative risk estimates.  Adjustment for overdispersion is available. The number of clusters is selected using (quasi-) information criteria. Methods for calculating cell-wise confidence bounds for stacked estimates are also provided.
